---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AppCard from '../components/AppCard.astro';
import apps from '../data/apps.json';

const windowsApps = apps.filter((app) => app.platform === 'Windows');
---

<Layout
	title="VTech App | Free Windows Utilities Coming Soon"
	description="VTech App builds practical free software utilities for Windows users, technicians, and system administrators. Windows tools are in development and Linux tools are planned."
>
	<section class="hero home-hero">
		<div class="hero-copy">
			<p class="eyebrow">Official vtech-app.com website</p>
			<p class="hero-motto">25 years of experience powered with AI capabilities.</p>
			<h1>Practical free software utilities for Windows administration.</h1>
			<p>
				VTech App builds focused tools for Windows users, technicians, and system administrators.
				New utilities will continue to be added as practical workflows are built, tested, and
				ready to release.
			</p>
			<div class="hero-actions">
				<a class="button primary" href="/apps/">Browse apps</a>
				<a class="button" href="/contact/">Send feedback</a>
			</div>
			<div class="category-chips" aria-label="Catalog categories">
				<a href="/apps/">Storage analysis</a>
				<a href="/apps/">Permission tools</a>
				<a href="/apps/">File server auditing</a>
				<span>Linux planned</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="feature-strip" aria-label="VTech App principles">
		<div class="feature-pill"><strong>Free</strong><span>No paid-service dependency</span></div>
		<div class="feature-pill"><strong>Static</strong><span>Fast Cloudflare Pages site</span></div>
		<div class="feature-pill"><strong>Useful</strong><span>Tools for real admin work</span></div>
		<div class="feature-pill"><strong>Direct</strong><span>Support via vtechinf1@gmail.com</span></div>
	</div>

	<section class="feature-grid" aria-label="Site highlights">
		<article class="card">
			<h2>Windows utilities</h2>
			<p>
				The catalog focuses on practical Windows administration workflows and will continue to
				grow as new utilities are ready.
			</p>
		</article>
		<article class="card">
			<h2>Downloads coming soon</h2>
			<p>
				Download buttons remain disabled until official builds are ready. No fake installers or
				placeholder packages are published.
			</p>
		</article>
		<article class="card">
			<h2>Feedback and suggestions</h2>
			<p>
				Use the contact form to request features, report issues, or suggest practical utilities
				that would help your workflow. You can also email vtechinf1@gmail.com directly.
			</p>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section class="catalog-panel">
		<div class="card catalog-stat">
			<div>
				<strong>3</strong>
				<span>Windows utilities in development</span>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<p class="eyebrow">Catalog status</p>
			<h2>Official downloads will appear only when releases are ready.</h2>
			<p>
				VTech App is currently a launch catalog and support hub. Each app has a detail page,
				release metadata, tags, screenshots, and a clear Coming Soon download state.
			</p>
			<div class="actions">
				<a class="button" href="/downloads/">View downloads</a>
				<a class="button" href="/apps/">View app catalog</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<div class="section-heading">
			<div>
				<p class="eyebrow">Windows apps</p>
				<h2>Utilities currently in development</h2>
				<p>
					Each app is marked Coming Soon until real release builds are available from official
					VTech App links.
				</p>
			</div>
			<a class="button" href="/apps/">View all apps</a>
		</div>
		<div class="grid">
			{windowsApps.map((app) => <AppCard app={app} />)}
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="two-column">
		<aside class="hero-panel terminal-window" aria-label="Project status">
			<div class="terminal-bar"><span></span></div>
			<p class="terminal-line"><strong>vtech-app.com</strong> status</p>
			<p class="terminal-line">&gt; catalog: windows utilities</p>
			<p class="terminal-line">&gt; downloads: coming soon</p>
			<p class="terminal-line">&gt; linux tools: planned</p>
			<p class="terminal-line">&gt; accounts: none</p>
			<p class="terminal-line">&gt; backend: static only</p>
		</aside>
		<article class="notice">
			<p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
			<h2>Questions, suggestions, and support.</h2>
			<p>
				Reach VTech App directly at <a href="mailto:vtechinf1@gmail.com">vtechinf1@gmail.com</a>.
				Use your own email client or the contact form on the Contact page.
			</p>
			<a class="button" href="/contact/">Contact VTech App</a>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section class="two-column">
		<article class="notice">
			<p class="eyebrow">Future platform</p>
			<h2>Linux utilities are planned.</h2>
			<p>
				The Linux catalog will stay empty until real utilities are ready to announce and release.
			</p>
		</article>
		<article class="notice">
			<p class="eyebrow">Support</p>
			<h2>Support independent free software.</h2>
			<p>
				Donations help cover development time, testing, hosting, and future releases while
				keeping VTech App tools free.
			</p>
			<a class="button primary" href="/donate/">Donate</a>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section class="final-cta">
		<div>
			<p class="eyebrow">Stay connected</p>
			<h2>Help shape future VTech App releases.</h2>
			<p>
				Send feedback, feature ideas, and practical Windows administration problems you want the
				tools to solve.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="actions">
			<a class="button primary" href="/contact/">Send feedback</a>
			<a class="button" href="/downloads/">Check downloads</a>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
